node.text: 35 y/o Lü Xiaojun (81kg, China) cleaning 208kg/458.5lb in a World Record attempt in his current hometown of Tianjin, China!  This was an attempt to break his own WR of 207kg from the 2019 WWC.  He’s currently battling with 21 y/o Li Dayin for the 81kg Olympic spot to represent China at the 2020 Olympic Games in Tokyo.

Chen Guiming (59kg, China) clean and jerking 138kg/304lb to set an int’l competition PR at the 2019 Tianjin World Cup!  Check out that depth on the jerk!
———
While this lift puts her on the list of the top 10 best ever C&Jers in the 58/59kg classes, she stands little chance of competing in the 2020 Olympic Games due to the 4 athlete per gender per country limit — China has five likely female gold medals in 49, 55, 64, 87 and +87 and the presence of Kuo (TPE) and Choe (PRK) make it unlikely that Chen would be considered for one of the four spots.

@kuohsingchun_official (60.13kg, @hkgrptaipei) clean and jerking 141kg/310lb at the 2019 Tianjin World Cup!  This is 1kg above her 59kg C&J world record and it’s 1kg below her int’l competition PR of 142kg set at the 2017 Universiade!

17 y/o @nina.sterckx (55kg, Belgium) snatching 88kg to set a Youth World Record in the snatch!  This happened at the 2019 European Youth Championships in Eilat and it adds to her 83kg Youth World Record snatch that she set in the 49s a few months ago at the 2019 European Juniors!

2016 Olympic Champion @dengweichina (64kg, China) snatching 117kg/258lb to set a new World Record at the 2019 IWF World Cup!  This matches the old 63kg WR held by @svetlana.tsarukaeva set at the 2011 WWC in Paris — that 63kg A session in Paris also happened to be the first ever session that we covered as a company.

@shi_zhi_yong (73kg, China) clean and jerking 198kg/436.5lb to set a new World Record at the 2019 IWF World Cup in Tianjin!  If/when he can make 200kg in the future, that would make him among the lightest lifters to ever make 200kg in int’l competition.  As far as we know, should Shi do it, the only lighter lifters in the 200kg club to make it past doping would be Mikhail Petrov and Alexander Varbanov.

@hojamuhammet (+109kg, @hkgrpturkmenistan) clean and jerking 242kg/533.5lb to set a PR at the 2019 WWC!
——
The super heavyweight male Olympic medal picture is very interesting once you get past the obvious gold medal going to Lasha.  While Gor seems like a likely silver medal, there are persistent rumors that Armenia has another drug positive coming down the pipe which would put them over the 20 positive limit (since Beijing 2008), thereby limiting them to one male spot.  If this is the case, it is safe to assume that Simon Martirosyan would be the male picked.  And given that Irakli Turmanidze does not have an event from period 2, that takes away another medal contender.  And while Edward Ziazulin seems capable, he’s also from a 1 athlete country and Belarus seems more likely to pick Aramnau.
——
This leaves @hojamuhammet, @rreisfernando, @alidavoudi__ (although Iran only has two male spots, so he’d need to be selected), @walid.bidani, @jiriorsag, etc to battle it out for two medal positions.  And @martseim is a contender if he can make it to Tokyo and get back to pre-injury shape.

@m_charron28 (64kg, @hookgripcan) clean and jerking a PR 128kg/282lb at the 2019 ODESUR Grand Prix!  With the first two 64kg Olympic medals seeming locked up by China (Deng Wei) and DPRK (Rim Un Sim), Charron will be battling with the likes of @tomaloredanaelena, @mercedespereztigrero and @angiedajomes for the final Olympic medal next summer in Tokyo.

@leidysolis76kg_oficial (Colombia) clean and jerking 145kg/319lb, just 1kg under her int’l competition PR, to win the 76kg category at the 2019 ODESUR Grand Prix.  She’s part of a closely matched group of 76s that will likely be battling for the silver/bronze (behind Rim Jong Sim’s likely gold) at the Tokyo 2020 Olympics — likely including Neisi Dajomes, Kate Nye, Lydia Valentin and Aremi Fuentes.  Darya Naumava and Iryna Dekha come from spot restricted countries but they could be factors if they get selected.

21 y/o @jhonatan.rivas.1998 (96kg, Colombia) clean and jerking 213kg/469.5lb to set a new PR at the 2019 ODESUR Grand Prix!  He also snatched 180kg so this was a PR 393kg total.  Another bit of good news is that now you can show this to anyone whining that they can’t C&J well because they’re tall with long legs.

@zacariasbonat (81kg, Dominican Republic) clean and jerking 205kg/452lb at the 2019 ODESUR Grand Prix in Lima!  This is the most any 81kg has C&Jed other than Lü Xiaojun and Li Dayin and it’s just 2kg shy of Lü’s world record.  It doesn’t seem like 208 is out of reach if he remembers to tighten his belt next competition!

19 y/o @yenny_sinisterra8 (55kg, Colombia) clean and jerking 116kg/255lb to set a Junior World Record at the 2019 WWC!  While her best total is currently probably a few kg away from an Olympic medal, she is young and improving quickly so she’s got a chance to move into the Olympic medals next summer if she can close out the quad strong.

@pachomos61kg (Colombia) clean and jerking 172kg/379lb — 2.82x his bodyweight!  This won him the silver medal 🥈 in the C&J and bronze medal 🥉 overall and he’s also a strong medal contender next year in Tokyo 2020.  He’ll also be competing on Friday in Lima, Peru at the 2019 ODESUR Grand Prix.

20 y/o @v_lalayan105 (+109kg, Armenia 🇦🇲) snatching 194kg/428lb at the 2019 Euro Jrs.  Just three years ago, he snatched 156kg at the 2016 Youth Worlds in Malaysia — we will post a video of that on our story.  In Bucharest, he also C&Jed 230kg/507lb on his second and passed on his 3rd so if you’re looking for the heir apparent to Gor and Ruben, this is the guy!

18 y/o @enzokuworge (+109kg, Netherlands) clean and jerking a PR 220kg/485lb at the 2019 Euro Juniors!  For some backstory, at 2017 Euro Youth he did 183kg, at 2018 Euro Youth he did 202kg and now he’s up to 220kg with two more full years to go as a junior!

20 y/o Eileen Cikamatana (87kg, Australia) clean and jerking an unofficial Junior World Record of 150kg/330lb at the 2019 European Juniors!  If you’re wondering why an Australian was lifting at Euro Juniors and why it’s unofficial, we are putting more details in the comments.
@kar_avyan (89kg, Armenia 🇦🇲) snatching 170kg/375lb to set a new European Junior record!  Crazy speed!  Too fast even for the new slow mo technology we are using at this meet.
@mirko_zanni (67kg, Italy) snatching 145kg/319lb to set a European U23 record!  #superveloce

20 y/o @aysegulcakinn (59kg, @hookgriptur) clean and jerking 116kg/255lb to win European Juniors for the second straight year!  And she did it with a PR C&J and total (203kg). Check out the crazy ankle mobility!

17 y/o @nina.sterckx (49kg, Belgium) going WTG with this 83kg/183lb snatch to set a new Youth World Record earlier today at the 2019 European Juniors!  Everyone young or old could use some of that Nina bottom position determination!

Om Yun Chol (55kg, DPRK) clean and jerking 166kg/366lb to win the 2019 WWC!  This is now the 7th time that he’s made triple bodyweight in int’l competitions, with four of them being world records: 2012 Olympics, 2013 Asian Interclub Championships (WR), 2014 Asian Games (WR), 2014 WWC, 2015 WWC (WR), 2016 Olympics and 2019 WWC (WR). It’s a bit difficult to check complete records but the only lifter who would have a chance of matching or exceeding seven 3x BW C&Js would be Naim Suleymanoglu, the Bulgarian-born all time great who competed mostly for Turkey in the 80s, 90s and early 00s.
The long awaited video of @talakhadzelasha_official clean and jerking 267kg/588.6lb in training in Batumi before 2019 Euros!  @doctor_giorgi 🥔 🎥

Front view of @tiantao96kg clean and jerking 230kg/507lb to win his first world title!  This was a do-or-die lift to beat @mesohassona.  Tian is probably on the Olympic bubble for China as 67/73/81 are very likely gold medals from Chen, Shi and Lu/Li, respectively.  The last class to be picked for their maximum 4 male team will likely either be 61 (Li Fabin) or 96 (Tian Tao) and probably depends a lot on @sohrab.moradiii.
